choices.text:
what are the verb tenses?
Sure, here they are! Verb tenses in English include: 
1. Present - "I go to bed."
2. Past Simple (Simple past) - "He left." 
3. Future Simple/Continuous (Future) - "They will buy bread tomorrow."
4. Present Continuous (Present participle or gerund) - "She is studying."
5. Past Participle (Gerundive, adverbial participle) - "The dog bit me yesterday." 
6. Future Perfect/Continuous (Future perfect continuous) - "They will be home all night long."
7. Present Perfect (Present perfect) - "I have been working hard today."
8. Past Continuous (Past progressive, or gerund of past participle forming a new verb in the third person singular present tense.) - "The sun set yesterday at noon." 
9. Future Perfect/Simple (Future perfect simple) - "They will have finished homework by tomorrow morning."
